CREATE A SCREEN OF TEXT BY TYPINGDATA  IN AND USING THE APPLEMONITOR'S ESCAPE COMMANDS (E.G.;<ESC>@ CLEARS THE       SCREEN).SAVE BY TYPING CTRL-S ANDRETURN.BLOAD THE FILE LATER TO RESTORE THESCREEN OF TEXT.  NOTE THAT SINCETHIS   PROGRAM LOADS AND SAVES THE'SCREEN     HOLES'; THERE MAY BESTRANGE SIDE       EFFECTS IF YOUARE USING PERIPHERAL     DEVICES.SEE ALSO THE 'NOTEPAD' PROGRAM.